aw is presented thoroughly and in detail. The manual not only is an introduction and overview but also provides further orientation as well as numerous case examples and solutions, and practical schemas.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aBankruptcyzGermany. 4aInsolvenzverfahren. 7aLAW / Bankruptcy & Insolvency.2bisacsh  aInsolvency proceedings.1 aSmid, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2007z9783110277135oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET RECHTSWISSENSCHAFTEN 2007z9783110276978oZDB-23-DGC40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311091693540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110916935423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110916935/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGCb2007  aZDB-23-DGGb2007  aZDB-23-GLAc2000d2014